definitions.definition: A beer brewed by enthusiasts rather than commercially.
Made or changed by amateurs (especially games or amateur radio equipment).
A player who plays for the team named after their own native town .

main_definition: A beer brewed by enthusiasts rather than commercially.
secondary_definitions: ( informal ) Made or changed by amateurs (especially games or amateur radio equipment).
( Canada , sports , countable ) A player who plays for the team named after their own native town .
